                     professionally.  We know that your commitment and performance will contribute directly to Experian’s
                     success. So, we recognise and celebrate individual effort, as well as team performances
                     and achievements.  We’re always looking for new ways to help our people achieve their potential
                     and aspirations. That means pushing the boundaries and challenging how we do things.  We listen to our employees and actively encourage your ideas and opinions.
                     It’s all about you developing your role and making it your own. Our business
                     offers a breadth of learning activities and programmes, so it’s up to you to
                     take the initiative and decide which skills you would like to enhance or develop.     Our people are our most valuable assets.  Our diverse workforce is part of the reason for our success. Our talent strategy
                     reflects our commitment to searching the globe for the very best individuals, so that
                     we can innovate and meet the needs of our increasingly diverse clients and consumers.
                     Our progressive policies, such as flexible working hours, ensure that our employees
                     can flourish regardless of their individual circumstance.  Our UK Gender Pay analysis  In our Gender Pay analysis report, you’ll find our results on the
                     following:   Gender pay gap (mean and median averages)  Gender bonus gap (mean and median averages)  Proportion of men and women receiving bonuses  Proportion of men and women in each quartile of the organisation’s pay structure   Gender Pay is an issue that we take very seriously at Experian. We’re focused
                     on creating greater balance and opportunity for women across our organisation –
                     not just in the UK, but around the world. In the report you’ll find both the
                     figures themselves and a deeper insight into life at Experian, showing the ways we
                     support diversity across organisation today.  View our full report  We are extremely focused on creating greater balance and opportunity for women
